3. References from openEMS (also GPL-3) — same caveats
---------------------------------------------------------------------

The `yaf_solvers/openems_adapter/` adapter imports the openEMS / CSXCAD
Python bindings at runtime and runs a real full-wave FDTD solve (see
`docs/HONEST_STATUS.md`). The GPL-3 considerations are therefore now
live and analogous to the necpp case above, with one practical
difference: openEMS upstream itself uses GPL-3 with an explicit
no-restriction stance on linking, but the safe assumption for
redistribution is still that combined works inherit GPL-3. As with
necpp, this repository does not bundle or redistribute openEMS / CSXCAD;
users build and install them separately, and the bindings are not a hard
dependency in `pyproject.toml`.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Reference projects under `_reference/` (not redistributed)
---------------------------------------------------------------------

During development, a number of open-source projects are shallow-cloned
into `_reference/` for study, never committed. The `_reference/`
directory is `.gitignore`d. None of those projects' source code is
included in this repository's tracked files.

